Uses of AuctionEvent in uk.ac.liv.auction.event
 

Subclasses of AuctionEvent in uk.ac.liv.auction.event
 class AgentPolledEvent
          An event that is fired whenever any agent is polled by an auction for its shout via the requestShout() method.
 class AuctionClosedEvent
          An event that is fired when an auction closes.
 class AuctionOpenEvent
          An event that is fired when an auction opens.
 class EndOfDayEvent
          An event that is fired at the end of every trading period.
 class RoundClosedEvent
          An event that is fired at the end of each round.
 class RoundClosingEvent
          An event that is fired at the end of each round, but before round-ending processing.
 class ShoutPlacedEvent
          An event that is fired every time a shout is placed in an auction.
 class ShoutReceivedEvent
          An event that is fired every time a shout is received in an auction (may not be accepted eventually), in contrast to ShoutPlacedEvent, which represents a shout is received and accepted.
 class TransactionExecutedEvent
          An event that is fired every time a good is sold in an auction.
